ServiceNow can host knowledge articles and FAQs to guide users. If the intake form links to a knowledge guide and shows required fields, that will reduce common errors. Knowledge articles can include examples like “what information is required for this type of request” and be surfaced in the ticket form.

Regarding systems: we should consider whether 3E can be the primary intake mechanism. In a perfect world, 3E would be used by PEs to submit pro formas with full visibility. But current 3E functionality is limited—some items aren’t visible in sent items or the pro forma locks, so you don’t see drafts. We need to explore 3E upgrade plans and integration options between 3E and ServiceNow to increase visibility and tracking. If 3E can generate tickets in ServiceNow or sync data, that would be ideal.

